Description: Neck and shoulder sherd of East Greek pottery closed vase, probably oinochoe; neck black; slightest ridge at turn; shoulder reserved; inscription cut on shoulder.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Found in the area between the sanctuaries of the Dioskouroi and Apollo (see Petrie 1886, 16)
Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Found in the area between the sanctuaries of the Dioskouroi and Apollo (see Petrie 1886, 16)
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 690)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 676, no. 350)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.446)
